The paper discusses the use of evolutionary robotics (ER) in web-based applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of WebGL and Javascript for 3D physics simulations suggests a potential fit for computer graphics (cs.GR) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of outreach to K-12 students and the general public implies a possible connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
